# Email Configuration for DataEvol.net Production
# Replace these with your actual Gmail credentials

# Gmail SMTP Configuration
SMTP_USER=your-dataevol-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-gmail-app-password

# Legacy support (for backward compatibility)
USER=your-dataevol-email@gmail.com
APP_PASS=your-gmail-app-password

# Instructions for Production Setup:
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to .env
# 2. Create a Gmail account for DataEvol (e.g., dataevol.contact@gmail.com)
# 3. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on the Gmail account
# 4. Generate an App Password:
#    - Go to Google Account Settings > Security > 2-Step Verification > App passwords
#    - Select "Mail" and generate a 16-character password
#    - Use this App Password (not your regular Gmail password)
# 5. Replace the values above with your actual credentials
# 6. All emails will be sent to: connect@dataevol.net
# 7. Test the configuration before deploying to production

# Example (replace with your actual values):
# SMTP_USER=dataevol.contact@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=abcd efgh ijkl mnop
